WEBVTT

00:15:58.888 --> 00:16:03.728
You know, if you were a songwriter,
25 years ago, you wrote a hit song,

00:16:03.752 --> 00:16:06.014
it got a million singles,

00:16:06.038 --> 00:16:09.559
you could get royalties
of around 45,000 dollars.

00:16:09.583 --> 00:16:11.899
Today, you're a songwriter,
you write a hit song,

00:16:11.923 --> 00:16:13.376
it gets a million streams,

00:16:13.400 --> 00:16:15.170
you don't get 45k,

00:16:15.194 --> 00:16:17.781
you get 36 dollars,

00:16:17.805 --> 00:16:19.752
enough to buy a nice pizza.

00:16:20.721 --> 00:16:22.099
So Imogen Heap,

00:16:22.123 --> 00:16:24.507
the Grammy-winning singer-songwriter,

00:16:24.531 --> 00:16:28.502
is now putting music
on a blockchain ecosystem.

00:16:28.526 --> 00:16:30.375
She calls it "Mycelia."